How to play any version of the game:
Look at the "Releases" part of this resperatory.
Open any release of the version you wanna play.
Click the top button, specifically; the button that says "Cubicles v(version type).html"
Now that you downloaded the version, either go to your files and click the file to play on your browser, or you can directly play when you  first downloaded the file.

These files are not meant to be open source, nor can and should they be used in other places, I kindly ask you dont claim the game as your own, nor you shouldnt use it in your projects.
But, you can record and make videos of the game as long as you credit me and of course, follow guidelines.

Entity Guide as of v0.1:
A-22: A-22 is a ambusher entity, so remember that.
A-22 has some rumbling and footstep sounds, and yeah hes a rusher entity too.

A-50 (its not A-60) :Hes pretty much the same as A-60

A-101: His spawn sound is pretty much a everyday sound, except its very echoey. And A-101 checks some grey lockers.

A-181: A-181 makes 1 out of 3 spawn sounds, and one of those coordinate to something it will do.
One sound means it checks grey lockers, another means it checks janitor closets, and the other one would check red lockers.
You will eventually figure out what the 3 sounds coordinate too.

A-200: It has a deep wind sound and nothing else, so keep your ears peeled. Otherwise; its just the same A-200.

A-220: It mimics A-200, and instead of just fallbacking; it would check some grey lockers.

A-350: Hes pretty simple, if you see him (Hes a eye), hide. His mechanic is just fallbacking but being freaking slow (lore fact: he goes very slow to mess with u)
also A-350 breaks the fourth wall so take note of that, and thats known especially since if he gets you he can genuinely close out the game tab.
